<DOC><DOCNO> AP890815-0064 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-08-15-89 0828EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r i PM-BRF--China-Corruption     08-15 0156</FIRST><SECOND>PM-BRF--China-Corruption,0161</SECOND><HEAD>Chinese Policewoman Executed for Taking Bribes</HEAD><DATELINE>BEIJING (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Authorities have executed a policewoman in Cantonfor taking tens of thousands of dollars in bribes, official reportssaid today.   Major state newspapers and television reports said thepolicewoman, Zhang Mayun, took bribes worth $56,150 in exchange forallowing people to remain in the southern city illegally.   She was sentenced to death on June 19, but the reports did notsay exactly when she was executed. Death sentences in China areusually carried out within a day or two with a bullet to the back ofthe head.   In another report, the English-language China Daily saidauthorities had received 172,000 tips from informants at corruptionreporting centers from January to June. The centers are part of amajor government anti-corruption drive.   The reports mentioned three pending cases of officials alsoaccused of taking bribes.   About 22,000 officials were accused of wrongdoing by theinformants.</TEXT></DOC>